cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG

This paper deals with the optimization of colormaps for accurate interpretation of scientific data, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Graphics (cs.GR), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the focus is on the visual perception of data, the first two sub-categories are the most likely.
